South Africa’s mobile operators have revealed pre-order contract prices for the Samsung Galaxy S9 and Galaxy S9+. The devices are set to launch on 16 March, and orders before 31 March will receive a R500 Samsung accessory voucher and six months of free Samsung Mobile Care cover. Different operators have also included other extras to sweeten their deals. Telkom has added voice minutes and 60GB of data valid for 3 months to its FreeMe 1GB plan, for example. The cash and contract deals on offer at the time of writing are shown below. Not shown in the tables is that Telkom’s FreeMe plans include free calls to any Telkom number, 10GB free Wi-Fi hotspot data, and free data for instant messaging. Certain FreeMe packages also receive Telkom’s LIT value-added services.